{
  "text": "Our results suggest that krill protein hydrolysates possess hepatoprotective effects against alcohol-induced liver damage, and thus, hydrolysates and bioactive peptides prepared from krill can be employed as functional foods to enhance liver functions and health. Further studies could focus on evaluating the anti-inflammatory potential of KPF using nuclear factor \u03baB (NF-\u03baB) pathway molecular mediators, which supposedly drive the major hepatic inflammatory reactions in Kupffer cells [CITATION_1] .",
